If you have perfect ingredients in the summertime, you don\rquote t have to do much to\par
them. With our perfect cherries [Michigan, while at Tribute restaurant], we\par
halved them, sprinkled them with sugar, and heated them with a blowtorch so\par
that they were just warmed through. The slightly caramelized sugar made a huge\par
difference in the flavor. I used a goat cream cheese worked to a texture similar to\par
mascarpone cheese, which I shaped into quenelles. Served alongside were some\par
ice wine vinegar caramel sauce and a crispy crepe. Before serving, I added\par
individual thyme leaves and a crack of black pepper. These are all really classic\par
flavors, especially the cheese with black pepper and cherries.\par
