Lemon zest adds a totally different dynamic than lemon juice. If you are making\par
an apple crisp, if you added a teaspoon of zest it would taste very different than\par
if you added lemon juice. The juice would make it taste tart, whereas the zest\par
would actually add a lemon flavor component to it. For ice cream, custards, and\par
tarts, use lemon juice. But if you are going to combine lemon with other flavors,\par
that\rquote s when you use zest.\par
