Use lemon juice when you want the acid and lemony flavor of the juice. If you\par
want the perfume of the lemon, use the zest because the skin is where you get\par
the essential oils. I use more lemon and orange than vanilla in my cooking\par
because they are more prevalent in Italy and in Italian cooking, and a flavor\par
profile that people recognize as Italian.\par
