I love lobster: poached, roasted, or grilled. I like mayonnaise or a vinaigrette\par
with my lobster much more than butter with lobster. In the summertime, I like it\par
with small potatoes and corn. I really like it with cilantro.\par
For my dish Roasted Maine Lobster in \ldblquote Folly of Herbs\rdblquote  with Baby Fennel and\par
Salsify, I wanted to do something different with lobster besides a lobster sauce. I\par
make a \ldblquote tea\rdblquote  of dried herbs: thyme, rosemary, fennel seeds, oregano, sage, mint,\par
and tarragon. This is boiled and strained, then gets a dash of Ricard [also known\par
as Pernod, an anise-flavored liquor]. The lobster gets finished with fresh parsley,\par
mint, and fresh oregano. I chose these two vegetables because salsify is\par
underused and underappreciated. I don\rquote t blanch my salsify in water because\par
when you do, the flavor stays in the water. I roast them and caramelize them a\par
little bit, then deglaze with just a little water with a sprig of thyme and a bay\par
leaf. Baby fennel is good because it plays off the Ricard and fennel. I quickly\par
blanch the fennel and then caramelize it.\par
