some mint to it, one of two things will happen: 1) Either you don\rquote t eat it, so\par
what\rquote s the point of putting it on the plate in the first place, or 2) If you do eat it,\par
that one mint leaf will completely change the balance of the dessert. If you have\par
a lemon tart that is mostly perfectly balanced lemon curd with a little whipped\par
cream and you add a mint leaf to the dessert, the leaf will play havoc with that\par
balance. So don\rquote t throw mint on a plate haphazardly, or you\rquote ll throw off the\par
balance of the entire dessert.\par
