On Selecting the Right Oil\par
Your choice of olive oil always depends on what you are using it for. In general,\par
you don\rquote t want an oil that is super-assertive, green, or peppery. You want a good\par
olive flavor. I use a 100 percent Italian blend. It is silly to cook with 100 percent\par
extra-virgin olive oil if you are just saut\'e9ing something. If the oil is going to stay\par
in what you are making, like a sauce, then start with extra-virgin olive oil. When\par
I make a tomato sauce, that is what I am starting with.\par
If you are finishing a dish, that is also when you would use an assertive, more\par
full-flavored oil. I also like to use nut oils, especially those made by Jean\par
Leblanc. They are insane; his oils are so good that after you taste them, nothing\par
else will do! I especially like to use nut oils in the fall. I use walnut oil dressing\par
on salads, especially those salads that accompany meat. If you make a foie gras\par
dish with apples and endive, an addition of walnut oil would be great.\par
