The salmon is roasted, and served with warm, slightly charred cucumbers,\par
which I like because they are rarely used cooked. We use market vegetables that\par
right now are bok choy and peas. I have added some trout caviar for a briny\par
flavor because salmon is on the sweet side. The dish is then finished with a\par
hickory broth.\par
For the hickory broth, we smoke some hickory chips, wrap them in\par
cheesecloth with juniper berries and peppercorns, and then submerge them in\par
water to make a broth. This creates a smoked sauce that is light and tasty. What\par
we have here is a \ldblquote wood stock\rdblquote  that makes perfect sense with the salmon\par
because so often salmon is smoked. After the wood comes out, you taste the\par
broth to adjust it. It may need some more water to cut the wood and smoke\par
flavor, or it might need to be reduced to intensify it. We finish the sauce with a\par
little half-and-half, and foam it with a handheld mixer.\par
